{
    "id": "rss-harvester",
    "name": "RSS Harvester",
    "tagline": "Polls RSS feeds on a schedule — AI relevance filtering surfaces only what matches your stated interests.",
    "description": "An LLM-enhanced producer worker that fetches one or more RSS/Atom feed URLs on a configurable schedule and pushes enriched `news.article` items onto the BFrost Item Bus.\n\nWhen you configure Interests, the worker asks the AI model to score each new article for relevance (1–5) and drops articles below your threshold. Items that pass get a clean 1–2 sentence AI-written summary and topic tags. Without interests configured (or when no model provider is set up), the worker falls back to publishing everything — same behaviour as v1.x.",
    "author": "@ccascio",
    "repoUrl": "https://github.com/ccascio/bfrost-workers",
    "category": "AI / Research",
